      "role": "user",
      "content": "fair enough. but if the \"underlying principles\" are so good, why does it always seem like the movement itself is the one pushing these strict new rules on how people are allowed to think or talk? feels like the \"social justice\" part is just being used as a shield to shut down any legitimate debate that doesn't fit a specific political agenda.",
